We love this recipe at our house and don't mind the "pale" meatballs (which, incidentally, are how the meatballs in a traditional Italian wedding soup always look). I have used Swiss chard often as a substitute for escarole, which I have a hard time finding here. I saute the stems of red Swiss chard in a little olive oil & garlic to soften before adding to the pot. Another tip: making a double batch of meatballs takes just a few minutes more than a single batch, and (uncooked) they freeze beautifully on a cookie sheet. I store in a freezer bag for an almost instant soup on a night with a time crunch.

